Name: San Fernando Valley East-West Transit Corridor
MOS-3
column10: MOS-3 originally had 3 components: A North Hollywood extension, East Side extension and the Mid-City extension. In addition, a phase 2 of the Eastside corridor was already in preliminary engineering. Due to budget issues 1998, all components were cancelled except the North Hollywood extension, which was opened in 2000. The East side corridor was renewed as a light rail project and renamed the Metro Gold Line Eastside Extension (#208)
